entry.title: Make XHR document.lastModified test handle summer to winter time change.
entry.content:
document.lastModified is a legacy API which is tricky to test because it

reports times in the local timezone, but without any timezone indicator.

Such times cannot be reliably converted to UTC, because times during the

hour on either side of the change from summer to winter time produce the

same local time string as times on the other side of the change.



This change moves the code in document-lastModified-01.html that already

deals with this complexity into a shared support script and then uses it

to fix the equivalent test in responsexml-document-properties.htm, which

still has failures around the change from summer time to winter time, as

document-lastModified-01.html used to have. This also renames the moved

function and constant to fit better in a separate support script.



Bug: 1382239

entry.title: Use WeakPointer for the loader fallback callback.
entry.content:
`MaybeStartLoader` binds an unretained pointer to

`FallbackToNonInterceptedRequest`, which is passed through a series of

objects until it reaches `ServiceWorkerMainResourceLoader`.



When "network" or "cache" is selected as a ServiceWorker static

routing API's source and caused the network fallback, the unretained

pointer can be released and may cause use-after-free.



This CL changes the unretained pointer to a weak pointer to avoid that.

For the consistency of the function call, both of the callbacks

starts to use weak pointers.



Bug: 1499298

entry.title: Sort all the document markers
entry.content:
To improve the efficiency of marker painting, it is desirable to

keep all markers sorted, including overlapping markers. This allows

us to avoid sorting markers at paint time, over and over again.



The existing UnsortedDocumentMarkerListEditor code is updated to

keep the markers sorted on StartOffset().



Additional testing for overlapping markers, particularly nested

markers, is added. Duplicate methods between the sorted and unsorted

marker editors are rationalized. Calling code is updated.



This CL does not change the code in DocumentMarkerController to

take advantage of the sort. That will be added in a follow on CL.

entry.title: Some WPT tests should run same-process only.
entry.content:
In preparation for enabling isolated sandboxed iframes by default, there

are some WPT tests that should not be allowed to run with origin process

isolation. In each case the affected tests are forced to remain same-

process by placing them in the not-site-per-process virtual test

suite.



drag-drop-same-unique-origin.html uses EventSender, and although its

src and target frames are same process, under isolated sandboxed iframes

that process would be remote to the mainframe, which EventSender will

not support.



The longtask* tests all use window.PerformanceLongTaskTiming, which

inherently does not support cross-process frames. The tests want to

exercise data coming from a cross-origin, same-site child frame, and

the safest way to ensure that is to force the frames to remain same-

process.



Note: the cross-origin longtask tests were using sandboxed-srcdoc

frames to simulate being cross-origin (and same-process, since WPT tests

default to process-per-origin), but there's no need for that if the

test is run in not-site-per-process. Therefore the tests have been

revised to be non-sandboxed cross-origin using WPT apis, resulting in

tests that are hopefully easier to understand.

entry.title: Use process behavior field in PrintingContext
entry.content:
In order to support a policy override for controlling out-of-process

printing, the low-level //printing layer cannot rely solely upon the

printing feature flags. Since policy preferences reside at a higher

level than //printing, this state information needs to be provided

to PrintingContext.



All logic under //printing which uses ShouldPrintJobOop() needs to be

changed. In some cases it is insufficient to just rely upon the

existing signal for whether system calls should be skipped, so a more

detailed signal is needed.



Replace the PrintingContext "skip system calls" mechanism with an enum

to identify the process behavior desired. This can provide the details

for whether OOP printing is involved in addition to whether system

calls should be skipped for the PrintingContext instance being created.



This API change ripples through the rest of the printing stack. This

prepares the upper levels of the printing stack to be ready to override

the behavior if OOP printing policy is specified.



Printing support in Pepper is unused, so this code no longer even needs

to check the feature flags. This code is just changed to use a

placeholder value of OOP disabled.

Test-only change. Before this CL, TestingProfile only accepted

BrowserContextKeyedServiceFactory testing factories via

```

Builder& AddTestingFactory(

BrowserContextKeyedServiceFactory* service_factory,

BrowserContextKeyedServiceFactory::TestingFactory testing_factory);

```

and

```

Builder& AddTestingFactories(const TestingFactories& testing_factories);

```

where

```

using TestingFactory =

base::RepeatingCallback(

content::BrowserContext* context)>;

```

RefcountedBrowserContextKeyedServiceFactory was not supported because

a) its testing factory returns scoped_refptr<>, not unique_ptr<>, and

b) it derives from RefcountedKeyedService, not KeyedService.





This CL adds:

```

Builder& AddTestingFactory(

RefcountedBrowserContextKeyedServiceFactory* service_factory,

RefcountedBrowserContextKeyedServiceFactory::TestingFactory

testing_factory);

```

and also makes the TestingFactories alias accept both types via

absl::variant.

entry.title: Fix EventSender tests that will break under isolated sandboxed iframes.
entry.content:
This CL updates a number of WPT tests that rely on EventSender, and that

will break when enable-isolated-sandboxed-iframes is enabled by default.

EventSender only works within a single renderer process, but the

affected tests will create situations where a parent cross-process to

a child will try and send and event using EventSender, and the event

will fail to reach the child.



The approach taken in this CL is to have the parent notify the child

via postMessage when an event is required, and the child will invoke the

event locally with EventSender. The revised tests will work correctly

regardless of whether enable-isolated-sandboxed-iframes is enabled or

not.
